column7: The central library on campus, Van Pelt has abundant study rooms, floors, and gorgeous study spaces, along with Mark's cafe and the 24/7 undergraduate study space.
One of the most beautiful and historic libraries on campus, and includes a free art exhibit.
Part of the engineering quad, Levine is home to many SEAS classes and OHs.
The newest section of the engineering quad, home to dark stone and green ceramic walls.
Built in 1954, DRL is home to all the Physics and Math classes/research for Penn.
A state-of-the-art study and information space that supports teaching and collaborative learning
A not as crowded as the others, lots of space and is slightly off campus!
Get a sushi bowl and chill in the huge lounging space!
Take a coffee break between classes.
Big, bright, well-lit space for photoshoots or work!
Come by for awesome people and learn more about PAACH, Makuu, and La Casa Latina. Or SABS in at Frontera!
A hidden gem next to DRL, great for quiet studying in a modern, new space.

column4: Papadakis Integrated Sciences Building, 3245 Chestnut St, Philadelphia, PA 19104
column7: Saxbys but near NCH and Shake Shack!

Newly renovated in 2017, Hill is now a busy hub for freshman! It has a dining hall, study spaces, a gym, dance studio, and even music practice rooms. There are 8 lounge spaces on each floor, 2 for each color quadrant.
Come buys school supplies or gear! Starbucks offers a large space upstairs.

column4: Jon M. Huntsman Hall, 3730 Walnut St, Philadelphia, PA 19104
column7: The central spot for any Wharton snek, Huntsman is home to 48 classrooms, 57 GSRs, Pret, the MBA Cafe, and much more; key to all club meetings and late night study sessions. Closes at 2AM!
Right next to the bridge, Perry World House is bright and spacious, hosting plenty of events centered around politics and world affairs.

column4: 3800 LOCUST WALK, 1920 COMMONS BLDG, Philadelphia, PA 19104
column7: With lots of tables and chairs, Starbucks is underneath the Commons dining hall.

column4: Class of 1920 Commons, 3800 Locust Walk, Philadelphia, PA 19104
column7: Has 3-4 tables and some couches for comfy work! Pick up your Amazon order while you're at it.
Right on Walnut Street, 39th Starbucks is a great place to grab a quick drink.
A popular boba store, Tea-Do has everything from asian snacks, fruit teas, to games!
Next to Frogro across from Cinemark, Metro is a hip fave. Space is on the smaller side.

column4: Ludlow St &, S 40th St, Philadelphia, PA 19104
column7: A short get away from campus, Green Line is known for food and good vibes.
One of the most popular high rises, Harnwell has a dance gallery and the dungeon, along with lounges every floor!
Another one of the three high rises, has Cafe Prima!
Another one of the three high rises, home to 784 undergraduates.
Du Bois strives to adhere to its original mission to support students of the African Diaspora by serving as a hub for activities that promote African and African American scholarship and culture.
The all upperclassmen counterpart to Stouffer Stouffer, Mayer boasts a tightly knit student group along with large room layouts.
Gregory celebrates diversity through its Modern Languages Program and cinema through the Film Culture series.

The central hub to all performing arts groups at Penn, Platt hosts amazing food and craft filled study breaks and events. There are plenty of music and dance studios, along with a free Keurig and tea.
Get an Acai bowl or smoothie with fresh fruit and toppings!
Consists of 3 college houses, 39 individual houses, and a dining hall; holds a vast majority of the freshman on campus.
Newly built in 2016, NCH is a 4 year house including a dining hall, music practice rooms, a media room, and tons of modern and beautiful amenities. Rooms are suite style.
A hidden spot inside the law school next to KCECH; super quiet and spacious for deep concentration.
A freshman dorm with a dining hall, library, and study spaces.
Penn's free modern art museum, boasting new exhibitions every month and event popups. Don't pass up this great museum!
A classic spot near high rises for coffee and seating.
